http://www.dft.gov.uk/consultations/dft-2012-36,Stopping Up and Diversion Orders: Reform of the Application Process for Local Highways,This consultation details proposals to simplify the process of applying for the stopping up and diversion of a highway.,"## Summary

Following the Penfold Review, this consultation details proposals to simplify the process of applying for the stopping up and diversion of a highway where this is required for the purpose of property development.

We propose to permit applications for a stopping-up or diversion order to be submitted at the same time as applying for planning permission for the proposed development (whereas under the existing legislation the developer can only apply after securing planning permission), and options for devolving decision-making to the local authority level.

## Consultation responses

### Interim Report considering implementation of option 1

Following the Penfold Review, the consultation offered three proposals to simplify the process of applying for the stopping up and diversion of a highway where this is required for the purpose of property development. The foundation of all three of the main policy options is a speeding up of the process by allowing stopping up and planning applications to run concurrently, namely option 1.

This interim report is considering only option 1, and therefore responses to question 3 of the consultation. The remaining options, for devolving decision-making to the local authority level and consultation responses, will be considered and a formal response and proposals for a way forward will be published by the end of November.

